 {"id":"bd-1jm0","title":"Add max_length to Prompt builder","description":"## Task Description

Add max_length configuration to the Prompt struct and integrate with read_line_limited.

## Implementation

### 1. Add field to Prompt struct

```rust
/// A prompt for user input with optional validation and default.
pub struct Prompt<T> {
    message: String,
    default: Option<T>,
    show_default: bool,
    markup: bool,
    validator: Option<Arc<dyn Fn(&str) -> bool + Send + Sync>>,
    parser: Option<Arc<dyn Fn(&str) -> Option<T> + Send + Sync>>,
    choices: Option<Vec<String>>,
    password: bool,
    max_length: Option<usize>,  // NEW: Maximum input length in bytes
}
```

### 2. Add builder method

```rust
impl<T> Prompt<T> {
    // ... existing methods ...

    /// Set maximum input length in bytes.
    /// 
    /// If input exceeds this limit, `ask()` returns `PromptError::InputTooLong`.
    /// 
    /// # Default
    /// 
    /// If not set, uses the default limit of 65536 bytes (64KB).
    /// Set to `usize::MAX` to effectively disable the limit (not recommended).
    /// 
    /// # Example
    /// 
    /// ```
    /// # use rich::interactive::Prompt;
    /// let prompt: Prompt<String> = Prompt::new("Enter short code")
    ///     .max_length(32);
    /// ```
    pub fn max_length(mut self, max_bytes: usize) -> Self {
        self.max_length = Some(max_bytes);
        self
    }
}
```

### 3. Define default constant

```rust
/// Default maximum input length for prompts (64KB).
const DEFAULT_MAX_INPUT_LENGTH: usize = 65536;

impl<T> Prompt<T> {
    fn effective_max_length(&self) -> usize {
        self.max_length.unwrap_or(DEFAULT_MAX_INPUT_LENGTH)
    }
}
```

### 4. Update ask() to use read_line_limited

Current (line ~218):
```rust
let mut reader = stdin.lock();
let mut raw_input = String::new();
reader.read_line(&mut raw_input)?;
```

After:
```rust
let mut reader = stdin.lock();
let raw_input = read_line_limited(&mut reader, self.effective_max_length())?;
```

### 5. Update Default impl

```rust
impl<T: Default> Default for Prompt<T> {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self {
            message: String::new(),
            default: None,
            show_default: true,
            markup: true,
            validator: None,
            parser: None,
            choices: None,
            password: false,
            max_length: None,  // Will use DEFAULT_MAX_INPUT_LENGTH
        }
    }
}
```

### 6. Add tests

```rust
#[test]
fn test_prompt_max_length_builder() {
    let prompt: Prompt<String> = Prompt::new("Test").max_length(100);
    assert_eq!(prompt.effective_max_length(), 100);
}

#[test]
fn test_prompt_default_max_length() {
    let prompt: Prompt<String> = Prompt::new("Test");
    assert_eq!(prompt.effective_max_length(), DEFAULT_MAX_INPUT_LENGTH);
}

#[test]
fn test_prompt_input_too_long() {
    // This test requires mocking stdin - see integration test approach
}
```

